div1.p:
Q. Do you know
Mary Banks
;

Mr. Nicholson. I live at Knightsbridge;
Elizabeth Law
lived servant with me, she is daughter-in-law to Mrs. Adams; the girl living with me, Mr. Eliott came to me with this bill of sale, and said, it was the girl's right; so I went to Mr. Darby, as he was a country man of mine, and sent him to Mrs. Adams, to make inquiry of her, concerning the will of the father, but found Eliott had given a wrong account.
